      "code_changes": [
        {
          "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/query.py\"}\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\", \"symbol\": \"QuerySet\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\", \"symbol\": \"ModelIterable\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\", \"symbol\": \"SQLCompiler\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/query.py\", \"symbol\": \"Query\"}\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\", \"symbol\": \"QuerySet.__iter__\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\", \"symbol\": \"QuerySet._fetch_all\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/query.py\", \"symbol\": \"ModelIterable.__iter__\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/query.py\", \"symbol\": \"Query.get_compiler\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\", \"symbol\": \"SQLCompiler.execute_sql\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"django/django\", \"path\": \"django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\", \"symbol\": \"SQLCompiler.as_sql\"}\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"Django implements lazy queryset evaluation through a multi-layer execution chain. When a QuerySet is iterated, the OperationalError occurs when the lazy-evaluated SQL query is first executed.\\n\\nLazy Queryset SQL Compilation:\\n\\n1. QuerySet (django/db/models/query.py:303) implements the lazy ORM interface. The class stores a Query object (_query attribute) that represents the SQL to be executed, but does not execute it immediately.\\n\\n2. The Query object (django/db/models/sql/query.py:226) encapsulates all SQL construction logic and provides get_compiler() (line 364) to obtain a compiler instance.\\n\\n3. Lazy evaluation is triggered when __iter__() is called on a QuerySet. The __iter__() method (django/db/models/query.py:396) immediately calls _fetch_all() to ensure results are cached before iteration.\\n\\n4. _fetch_all() (django/db/models/query.py:2093) instantiates the queryset's iterable class (by default ModelIterable) and iterates over it, causing SQL compilation and execution.\\n\\nDatabase Query Execution (Where OperationalError is Raised):\\n\\n5. ModelIterable (django/db/models/query.py:88) is the iterable class responsible for executing the database query. Its __iter__() method (line 91) calls compiler.execute_sql() to run the compiled SQL.\\n\\n6. The compiler is obtained by calling queryset.query.get_compiler(using=db) (line 94 in ModelIterable.__iter__). This returns an SQLCompiler instance.\\n\\n7. SQLCompiler (django/db/models/sql/compiler.py:40) is the main compiler class that handles SQL generation and execution. It has two critical methods:\\n   - as_sql() (line 763): Compiles the Query into SQL string and parameters\\n   - execute_sql() (line 1601): Executes the compiled SQL against the database\\n\\n8. execute_sql() is where the OperationalError is triggered. The method:\\n   - Calls self.as_sql() (line 1618) to compile the SQL query\\n   - Gets a database cursor (line 1629)\\n   - Executes the query via cursor.execute(sql, params) (line 1631) - THIS IS WHERE OperationalError IS RAISED\\n   - Handles the cursor results and returns them\\n\\nThe key chain of execution is: QuerySet.__iter__() \u2192 QuerySet._fetch_all() \u2192 ModelIterable.__iter__() \u2192 SQLCompiler.execute_sql() \u2192 cursor.execute() where the database error is raised.\"\n}\n",
